content: Use this space to discuss the relative merits and demerits of each plan from your assigned perspective in step 2. That was the step where you were asked to write an individual proposal and post it to the discussion forum. Work towards a consensus on which plan you think is the best as a group. Wherever possible, supplement plan suggestions, agreements and disagreements with reasons, and try to refer to or build upon your teammates' ideas.
I think that option 2 is the best. Outside of perhaps nuclear, it seems to be quite sustainable and make the least impact on the environment and water supply. Plus it is the cheapest
I completely agree about Plan 2. No waste disposal cost, no carbon tax, and the renewable tax credit is great.
i agree with plan two as well
its close between 2 and 3 for me
Plus, looking at the numbers, it is the second cheapest to implement. The only reason Plan 1 is so much cheaper is because it is based on 40% coal.
yeah exactly, my proposal in the beginning was on nuclear, but after seeing these cost analyses it'd be stupid not to do wind
i thought hydro would be cheaper than nuclear and coal, i thought wrong
I think with hydro its the huge cost of a dam
When we first started I had nuclear in mind as well, but the more I read as we progressed led me to either wind or hydro. With the math in front of us, wind is a no-brainer.
Material cost and LABOR cost to build it.

yeah thats me. Just figured we need to get something there haha

Thank you for participating in the discussion. You now have just 5 minutes to finalize a joint argument in favor of one plan and complete your proposal on the left. Keep in mind that you will be evaluated solely based on the quality of your proposal (i.e., the thoroughness of the reasoning displayed).
